<title><![CDATA[Google's designers on why the Pixel Fold isn't just another foldable]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>自<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-04-22-samsung-galaxy-fold-review-expensive-experiment.html">2019 年发布初代 Galaxy Fold</a>以来，三星基本上垄断了带有可弯曲屏幕的大型手机。但随着本月晚些时候<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-officially-reveals-the-pixel-fold-174726500.html">Pixel Fold</a>即将面世，谷歌希望打破这一束缚。也就是说，由于三星已经发布了四代旗舰折叠屏手机，谷歌无法简单地重复竞争对手的设计。在 Pixel Fold 发布前的一次采访中，谷歌的两位产品经理 (PM)——George Hwang 和 Andrea Zvinakis——坐下来就现在的原因、公司的不同之处以及即将推出的柔性手机将产生怎样的影响发表了一些见解未来的设备。</p><p>我在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-fold-hands-on-finally-a-real-rival-for-samsungs-foldables-185253034.html">动手</a>时首先注意到的是 Pixel Fold 的形状。谷歌没有采用类似于<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-4-review-specs-price-a-flagship-foldable-refined-131543810.html">Galaxy Z Fold 4</a>的又长又细的警棍状底盘，而是选择了形状更像护照的更宽的框架，这是谷歌的有意决定。 Pixel Fold 团队的 PM Hwang 告诉我，“当我们谈论 Pixel Fold 时，我们通常首先谈论外部显示屏。” </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/5e6c4760-0bd8-11ee-bf93-f2376fecac9f" style="height:1152px;width:2048px;" alt="工程师的草图显示了 Pixel Fold 的一些内部工作原理。" data-uuid="e7ae2ba4-a284-36cf-ba6b-ea6463e71503"><figcaption>在此设计草图中，您可以看到 Pixel Fold 的铰链位于设备的最边缘，这极大地影响了手机的整体设计</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>Hwang 说，这是因为人们与手机进行的互动中，超过 50% 的互动时间都不到两分钟——比如给朋友发短信、换歌或简单地设置闹钟。 “我们对外形因素的关注至关重要，而且是有意为之，以确保我们提供可用的外部显示屏，以便您可以随心所欲地使用手机。”</p><p>虽然像普通手机一样使用 Pixel Fold 的外部显示屏听起来很明显，但也有点令人惊讶。通常，当人们讨论可折叠设备时，大部分注意力都集中在内部那个精美的柔性屏幕上。但更重要的是，这触及了谷歌对 Pixel Fold 的一些总体设计目标：能够像普通手机一样使用它，即使你只是关闭它使用它，允许用户打开折叠以增强他们的体验，然后确保即使它是一个更大的设备，它仍然是一个可行的日常驱动程序。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/8f51ac80-0bd8-11ee-bff7-2c3616f87e40" style="height:1500px;width:3000px;" alt="在 Engadget 关于 Pixel Fold 的采访中，我们采访了谷歌的两位产品经理：George Hwang（左）和 Andrea Zvinakis（右）。" data-uuid="790a9e67-37c9-30af-a68e-df5c4866fa74"><figcaption>在 Engadget 关于 Pixel Fold 的采访中，我们采访了谷歌的两位产品经理：Pixel Fold 团队的 George Hwang（左）和 Android 平台团队的 Andrea Zvinakis（右）。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>至于使用那个大的内部显示屏来增强设备的功能，感觉 Pixel Fold 的大部分潜力在于硬件和软件之间的结合。作为在谷歌 Android 平台团队工作的人，Zvinakis 强调了 Pixel Fold 的连续性和姿态的重要性。 “如果我们只是为平板电脑设计，你可以只创建一个大屏幕，”他说，“而对于可折叠设备，你通常需要展开才能继续进行会议。”</p><p>在为可折叠设备设计应用程序或用户界面时，谷歌需要考虑按钮或其他可能落在 Pixel Fold 折痕中的元素。但这也意味着能够在不丢失位置的情况下打开设备，这通常感觉像是一个难以实现的目标。但是当它工作时，它提供了一种即时适应性的感觉，这是传统手机无法获得的。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/f6b73f70-0bd8-11ee-9fbf-27405f03869f" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="对于 Pixel Fold，谷歌的主要目标之一是创造一个 5.8 英寸的外部显示屏，它比竞争对手手机上的类似产品更有用。" data-uuid="ec42528c-d948-3419-9af3-87ef265f65d4"><figcaption>对于 Pixel Fold，谷歌的主要目标之一是让手机的 5.8 英寸外部显示屏尽可能实用，这样人们就不会觉得被迫使用更大的主显示屏来完成某些任务。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>连续性也会影响姿势，即手机屏幕从打开到关闭的位置以及两者之间的每个角度。由于 Pixel Fold 的灵活设计，谷歌不仅需要跟踪设备的方向，还需要预测手机摄像头和用户界面等组件如何根据其姿势进行调整、移动和行为。 Zvinakis 说：“我们希望展开设备能给用户带来好处，而不仅仅是看到扩展的手机布局。” “这就是为什么我们创建了诸如双色通知之类的东西来利用显示器的两侧。”</p><p>但更令人兴奋的是 Zvinakis 说姿势检测可以解锁全新的用例，例如 Pixel Fold 上的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://youtu.be/9wobcM-WPQk?t=79">双屏解释器模式</a>。这允许用户将手机放在一个位置，以便两个人可以实时看到不同语言的翻译——每个人都有自己的显示器——这减少了当每个人都必须共享一个单一的时发生的典型的来回屏幕。虽然我们已经看到可折叠手机的其他一些新颖用途，例如在使用手机外部显示屏的同时使用后置摄像头拍摄高分辨率自拍照，但可折叠手机提供的功能越来越多，而这些功能在使用传统手机时根本无法获得玻璃砖。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/33af4f80-0bd9-11ee-a77b-edc791b42597" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="虽然 Pixel Fold 是一款大型设备，但谷歌专注于将其做得极薄（小于 6 毫米），这样它仍然感觉像是一个可行的日常驾驶者。" data-uuid="65250d37-ddc0-3e03-8ffe-97c2968fda2e"><figcaption>虽然 Pixel Fold 是一款大型设备，但谷歌专注于将其做得极薄（小于 6 毫米），这样它仍然感觉像是一个可行的日常驾驶者。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>可折叠产品发挥其真正潜力还需要其他元素。以 Fold 的任务栏为例，它需要跨越启用短移动交互和更复杂的多任务处理情况之间的界限。 “我们在去年 3 月推出了<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/android-12-l-hands-on-some-big-multitasking-upgrades-but-is-it-enough-180002295.html">Android 12L</a>的任务栏，第一个版本基本上是一个固定的任务栏，你必须长按才能隐藏，长按才能显示，”Zvinakis 说。 “但随着我们进行更多测试，用户表示他们发现这种行为有点笨拙。因此，我们将其改进为一个更短暂的任务栏，您可以在其中快速滑动访问它，将任何应用程序拖到分屏中，然后在您不使用它时它会自动关闭。”</p><p>最大的挑战是结合相互竞争的设计元素，例如设备的薄度，同时仍然支持复杂的组件，例如手机的 5 倍光学变焦。因此，为了克服困难，Hwang 向团队提出了一项挑战，即制造一种不仅仅是组件集合的设备：“如果你不想每天都使用它，那么它就不是我们想要的设备船。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/606effc0-0bd9-11ee-bbff-48aa4533192b" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="对于像 YouTube 这样优化了桌面模式的应用程序，Pixel Fold 能够准确检测其姿势非常重要，包括屏幕的方向和位置。" data-uuid="6f36a521-7118-3d4b-9f40-fae77569cb9a"><figcaption>对于像 YouTube 这样优化了桌面模式的应用程序，Pixel Fold 能够准确检测其姿势非常重要，包括屏幕的方向和位置。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>与其他手机相比，可折叠手机对薄度的追求更为重要。 Hwang 说：“我们意识到，如果这个东西又厚又笨重，你就不会真的想整天把它放在口袋里。”“我认为关键的推动因素是铰链。铰链是如何“architected 驱动可折叠显示器周围的一切。这是一种共生。”</p><p>这是一个有点出乎意料的启示，因为作为拥有多代 Galaxy Z Fold 系列的人，我认为<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-10-14-samsung-galaxy-fold-redesign-review-durability-screen.html">在原始模型的所有问题</a>之后铰链问题已经解决。 “你在大多数可折叠设备中看到的是，你会在三到四个不同的位置在铰链的整个长度上安装铰链机构，”Hwang 说。 “但问题是，现在你在设备的中间有铰链组件，这会增加我们所说的堆叠的厚度，然后你的显示器就在上面。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/02e29cb0-eef4-11ed-baee-b10bb903b80b" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Pixel Fold 的内部显示屏采用横向设计，无需旋转手机即可更好地观看电影。" data-uuid="4ab5b21e-7b78-3efb-988b-89a17b442328"><figcaption>虽然 Pixel Fold 的柔性显示屏确实有折痕，但谷歌对屏幕的折叠几何形状做了一些创新，以尽量减少其外观。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sam Rutherford/Engadget 摄</div></figure><p>所以 Hwang 认为“如果这些是限制因素，那么我们有没有办法创造性地将这些组件转移到其他地方？”因此，最终 Pixel Fold 团队所做的是将手机的两个铰链重新定位到设备的最边缘，使其脱离平面，这产生了许多重要影响。她说，这不仅减少了厚度，“它还有助于驱动外部 5.8 英寸显示屏和内部 7.6 英寸柔性内部屏幕之间的最大增量。”最重要的是，谷歌的架构帮助解决了 Hwang 所说的折叠几何问题，它描述了屏幕在铰链内的实际弯曲方式。 “铰链让我们能够将显示屏向内收起，让折叠延伸到该区域以进一步降低厚度，”她补充道。虽然到目前为止我只短暂地使用过 Pixel Fold，但结果相当惊人，谷歌能够制造出一款可以完全折叠的手机，同时厚度仍小于 6 毫米（合上时仅为 12.1 毫米）。</p><p>像 Pixel Fold 的铰链和薄度这样的进步并非没有权衡取舍。但是，虽然它的边框比三星的要大一些，但对 Hwang 来说还是值得的。 “边框让我们有机会拥有纯粹的显示屏，而无需显示屏下摄像头，我们认为这真的很酷。”它还为谷歌提供了更多余地来提高 Pixel Fold 的整体耐用性，其中包括 IPX8 防水等级。 “此外，它还符合人体工程学，更大的显示屏边框为您的双手提供了一个休息区，”她说</p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/02e29cb0-eef4-11ed-89ff-a5ecf71b593e" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="尽管 Pixel Fold 比 Galaxy Z Fold 4 重一点点，但它更时尚，尺寸更宽，这意味着它不会感觉那么厚重。" data-uuid="0f4cd6d6-a824-3e7b-b53d-7c3b074551c3"><figcaption>虽然这听起来可能没什么大不了的，但 Pixel Fold（右）的设计更薄，并且在关闭时屏幕之间没有间隙，这大大有助于使其易于使用。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sam Rutherford/Engadget 摄</div></figure><p>Hwang 说，处理 Pixel Fold 显示屏不可避免的折痕是另一种平衡行为，他仍然经常考虑这一点。 “它没有吸引力，但更大的问题是我们如何减轻折痕？我们如何最小化它？”最终，谷歌决定采用一种混合方法，产生一种更像是沿着屏幕长度延伸的微型水滴的折叠，而不是完整的折痕，这样可以减少它的外观，同时也可以防止随着时间的推移形成难看的沟槽。</p><p>尽管如此，尽管 Pixel Fold 的设计令人印象深刻，但在与谷歌产品经理交谈后，我觉得它有一个更重要的工作，作为未来可折叠设备的大使，并作为 Android 中具有前瞻性软件功能以及新优化的旗手应用。这是因为除了设备本身，Pixel Fold 还引入了一组全新的资源来帮助应用程序开发者优化他们的工作。 Zvinakis 说，“我们这样做的关键方法是通过开发人员指南、开发人员工具和易于使用的库。”这些东西决定了对自适应分辨率、横向、多任务行为等功能的支持。甚至还有单独的层表示开发人员为支持折叠友好功能所做的工作以及 Android Studio 仿真环境中可用的示例配置。 “我们即将在 Android Studio 中为这些 Google 设备推出物理设备流，这基本上意味着开发人员可以直接从您的 IDE（集成开发人员环境）中查看他们的应用程序如何在 Google 托管的 Pixel Fold 和 Pixel Tablet 设备上运行.我们只是想让开发人员真正轻松地测试这些新产品。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/02e2c3c1-eef4-11ed-b568-af03fce49730" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Pixel Fold 具有 5 倍远摄变焦功能，就像您在 Pixel 7 Pro 上获得的一样。" data-uuid="56cd4256-c66b-3f6e-acea-a71f49965848"><figcaption>与三星 Galaxy Z Fold 4 的变焦比 S22 Ultra 更短不同，Pixel Fold 具有与 Pixel 7 Pro 相同的相机系统，包括 5 倍光学变焦。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Sam Rutherford/Engadget 摄</div></figure><p>为了确保用户更容易找到这些应用程序，Zvinakis 表示谷歌将开始“在 Play 商店中更突出地展示真正高质量的应用程序，包括显示新的可折叠特定功能的屏幕截图。”所有这一切都伴随着 50 多个针对可折叠设备进行了优化的第一方 Google 应用程序，Hwang 和 Zvinakis 都表示这并非易事。通过这种方式，Pixel Fold 不仅可以作为未来设备的试验台，还可以作为谷歌不断发展的软件设计的试验台。</p><p>不幸的是，Pixel Fold 背后的团队未能克服所有可能阻止人们加入灵活手机趋势的障碍——尤其是其 1,800 美元的价格）。但即使 Fold 是该公司在该领域的首款产品，很明显谷歌在硬件和软件方面都为该领域带来了大量新创意。它纤薄、时尚，与 Z Fold 4 不同，Pixel Fold 提供与 Pixel 7 Pro 相同的出色相机体验。它的销售情况还有待观察，但三星的 Z Fold 在过去几年基本上停滞不前，Pixel Fold 的到来恰逢其时。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4d271ea7-dc27-4d24-b633-f6b76bb41f9d</guid><dc:creator>萨姆卢瑟福</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 16 Jun 2023 15:30:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686928265</ingested><modified> 2023-06-16T15:11:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e9689610-0bac-11ee-9fef-6f3a78593b6d" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e9689610-0bac-11ee-9fef-6f3a78593b6d" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Google]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The $1,800 Pixel Fold is Google's first attempt at making a foldable phone.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google Pixel Fold]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta's Voicebox AI is a Dall-E for text-to-speech]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>今天，我们距离长久以来承诺的不朽名人未来又近了一步（ <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/immortal-hologram-celebrities-chatgpt-ai-deep-fake-back-catalogs-180030493.html">自 4 月以来</a>）。 Meta 推出了 Voicebox，它的生成式文本转语音模型有望为口语词做 ChatGPT 和 Dall-E 恭敬地为文本和图像生成所做的事情。</p><p>从本质上讲，它是一个文本到输出的生成器，就像 GPT 或 Dall-E 一样——只是它不是创建散文或漂亮的图片，而是吐出音频剪辑。 Meta 将该系统定义为“一种非自回归流匹配模型，经过训练可以在给定的音频上下文和文本的情况下填充语音。”它已经接受了超过 50,000 小时未过滤音频的训练。具体来说，Meta 使用了一系列以英语、法语、西班牙语、德语、波兰语和葡萄牙语编写的公共领域有声读物的录音和抄本。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>据研究人员称，无论各方使用何种语言，这种多样化的数据集都允许系统生成更多的对话语音。 “我们的结果表明，在 Voicebox 生成的合成语音上训练的语音识别模型的性能几乎与在真实语音上训练的模型一样好。”更重要的是，与现有 TTS 模型所见的 45% 到 70% 的下降相比，计算机生成的语音执行时的错误率仅为 1%。</p><p>该系统首先被教导根据周围的片段以及段落的抄本来预测语音片段。 Meta 研究人员解释说：“在学会从上下文中填充语音后，该模型可以将其应用于语音生成任务，包括在录音中间生成部分，而无需重新创建整个输入。”</p><p>据报道，Voicebox 还能够主动编辑音频剪辑，消除语音中的噪音，甚至替换说错的词。研究人员说：“一个人可以识别出语音的哪个原始片段被噪音（如狗叫声）破坏，对其进行裁剪，并指示模型重新生成该片段，就像使用图像编辑软件清理照片一样.</p><p>文字转语音生成器已经面世一分钟——它们就是您父母的 TomTom 能够用摩根·弗里曼的声音给出不可靠的驾驶方向的方法。像<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://speechify.com/">Speechify</a>或<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://beta.elevenlabs.io/">Elevenlab 的 Prime Voice AI</a>这样的现代迭代功能要强大得多，但它们仍然在很大程度上需要大量的源材料才能正确地模仿他们的主题——然后为每一个提供另一堆不同的数据。单身的。其他。您希望它接受培训的主题。</p><p> Voicebox 没有，这要归功于一种新颖的零镜头文本到语音训练方法 Meta 调用流匹配。据报道，Meta 的 AI 在可理解性（1.9% 的单词错误率对 5.9%）和“音频相似性”（SOA 的 0.580 的综合得分为 0.681）方面均优于当前的技术水平，因此基准测试结果并不接近，同时运行速度比当今最好的 TTS 系统快 20 倍。</p><p>但是，不要让你的名人导航员排队，目前 Voicebox 应用程序及其源代码都不会向公众发布，Meta 周五证实，尽管“许多令人兴奋的用途”，但仍存在“滥用的潜在风险”生成语音模型的案例。”相反，该公司发布了一系列音频示例（见上/下）以及该程序的初始研究论文。未来，研究团队希望这项技术能够应用于声带损伤患者的假肢、游戏中的 NPC 和数字助理。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/metas-voicebox-ai-is-a-dall-e-for-text-to-speech-150021287.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/metas-voicebox-ai-is-a-dall-e-for-text-to-speech-150021287.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 55858da8-b42a-48e1-b9ae-98e479d66e02</guid><dc:creator>安德鲁·塔兰托拉</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 16 Jun 2023 15:00:21 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686853416</ingested><modified> 2023-06-15T18:23:42+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Andrew Tarantola]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/53dca6c0-0ad7-11ee-bdff-97d6ad440b00" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/53dca6c0-0ad7-11ee-bdff-97d6ad440b00" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Meta]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[buncha multicolored discs inline like a cross section of a waveform]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[voicebox top art]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gifts to upgrade your grad’s tech setup]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>每年春天，世界上都会涌现一批新的毕业生，其中许多人携带的是多年来经久不衰的小玩意儿。传统上，毕业是送礼的重要时刻——所以如果你认识一个即将进入现实世界的新毕业生，他可以在接受四年（或更多！）长时间的高等教育后升级，这里有很多礼物创意这将是对他们值得信赖但陈旧的技术的重大改进。</p><h2>笔记本电脑</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/8f645890-0318-11ed-abe7-4a5445793bdd" style="" alt="MacBook Air（M2，2022 年款）" data-uuid="a0241223-6c3b-3876-aa52-063f2dd61c28"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</div></figure><p>与平板电脑和智能手机一样有用，当您真正想要完成工作时，没有什么比传统笔记本电脑更好的了。这也是个人购买，因此在您扣动扳机之前，您需要知道收件人是喜欢 Windows、Mac 还是 Chrome OS。但是一旦你解决了这个问题，这些笔记本电脑就是市场上最好和最全面的选择。除非您要购买的人有一些<em>非常</em>具体的需求，否则这些机器中的一台可能符合要求。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>多年来，我们一直认为戴尔的 XPS 13 是整体上最好的 Windows 笔记本电脑，这一点没有改变。至此，戴尔几乎已经完善了它的工业设计：轻薄，但不以牺牲电量或电池寿命为代价。键盘和显示屏非常出色，您可以获得令人印象深刻的规格而无需花很多钱。一个缺点是戴尔似乎已经完全转向只有两个 USB-C 端口且没有耳机插孔的设计，这可能会有点限制。但撇开这些问题不谈，XPS 13 仍然是一个绝佳的选择。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dell;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b1bb23c9-a2d4-4e4e-bfac-7a560ebe7641&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dell&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASKc4GqWDhFab-twR4hxI-ih5JFMpujsE6mzzwGzCEFb&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dell.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fdell-laptops%2Fxps-13-plus-laptop%2Fspd%2Fxps-13-9320-laptop%2Fxn9320fplqh">XPS 13 Plus</a>配备英特尔第 12 代酷睿 i7 处理器、16GB RAM 和 512GB 存储空间，是一份可以让他们使用多年的笔记本电脑礼物。它还包括一个 3,456 x 2,100 分辨率的触摸屏，整个包装的价格非常合理，目前直接从戴尔购买，价格为 1,299 美元。</p><p>不过，对于玩游戏的人，我们建议换个方向。华硕 ROG Zephyrus G14 仍然是我们最喜欢的游戏笔记本电脑，它结合了相对便携性（3.5 磅和 14 英寸屏幕）和强大的功能。在我们的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/asus-zephyrus-g14-review-amd-ryzen-radeon-173016459.html">评论</a>中，我们说笔记本电脑非常引人注目，即使它比以前更贵。它拥有强大的 AMD 处理器和显卡，以及出色的显示屏、舒适的键盘、宽敞的触控板和坚固的设计。它不是电池寿命的冠军，但我们有 7 小时的非游戏使用时间 - 考虑到规格相当不错。 </p><p><core-commerce id="c59709504fb64676aae2bfdc2d219bfd" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="4d6e21848bb74c5aba3243fb8ea297af" data-type="product-list"></p><p>与华硕产品的通常情况一样，您可以获得多种配置的 Zephyrus G14，但我们推荐的配置包括 AMD Ryzen 9 6000 系列处理器、Radeon RX 6700S 显卡、16GB 内存、1TB SSD 和具有 120 赫兹刷新率的 2,560 x 1,600 显示屏。它目前在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Best Buy;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5e0bed65-d2f8-4b34-9b8f-955218c0e37a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Best+Buy&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAexMKSSz-aVrWQa7fVBbSK-T8yiqcCJ_FONcaMEe_M2u&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Fasus-rog-zephyrus-14-wqxga-120hz-gaming-laptop-amd-ryzen-9-16gb-ddr5-memory-amd-radeon-rx-6700s-1tb-pcie-4-0-ssd%2F6494638.p%3FskuId%3D6494638%26irclickid%3D3Vp23-S0nxyNWkASYIQzZw55UkAXQsUBw113TE0%26irgwc%3D1%26loc%3DSkimbit%2520Ltd.%26acampID%3D0%26mpid%3D10078">Best Buy 的</a>售价为 1,650 美元，它将提供强大的功能来处理现代游戏以及离开学校带来的所有“现实生活”任务。</p><p>对于喜欢 Mac 的人来说，Apple 的产品线可能出奇地复杂。然而，今年的选择是明确的。 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS8yMDIyLUFwcGxlLU1hY0Jvb2stTGFwdG9wLWNoaXAvZHAvQjBCM0JWV0o2WS8_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby15NC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzc5ZjE5OWEtYzgyMS00ZmIxLTkzMjEtMGZlMDgwYzIwYjRkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAZfoH4NrE9JEpQp4A4AiYQOGGqoMu8xohTHmBrc6P8Wc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2F2022-Apple-MacBook-Laptop-chip%2Fdp%2FB0B3BVWJ6Y%2F%3Fth%3D1">M2 驱动的 MacBook Air</a>是我们认为最适合大多数人的笔记本电脑，它是一款功能极其强大的电脑，不会像 MacBook Pro 那样花大钱。</p><p> Apple 去年夏天彻底重新设计了 MacBook Air，使其硬件让人联想到 14 英寸 MacBook Pro 和 M2 处理器。它感觉比它所取代的 M1 Air 更现代，并且有许多值得注意的改进，例如更好的网络摄像头、MagSafe 充电、M2 处理器，以及更大更好的显示屏。它仍然保留了 Air 的特征，不过，它非常轻巧便携，电池续航时间比市面上几乎所有笔记本电脑都长。</p><p>大多数人可能希望选择 1,699 美元的配置，包括 512GB 存储空间、16GB RAM 和带有 10 核 GPU 的 M2 芯片。虽然我们认为 Air 对大多数人来说已经足够了，但如果您对视频编辑等处理器密集型任务有浓厚兴趣，那么<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJTSERWQlhaP3RoPTEmdGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8teTQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3OWYxOTlhLWM4MjEtNGZiMS05MzIxLTBmZTA4MGMyMGI0ZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAYdivIfXymzKM9ckiDAc_gqk7WOMRzBCt9vWKtTrKFFw&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BSHDVBXZ%3Fth%3D1">1,999 美元的 MacBook Pro</a>值得考虑。它为您提供更强大的 M2 Pro 芯片，配备 16 核 GPU 以及华丽的 mini-LED 显示屏等其他优点。</p><p>鉴于 Chromebook 在教育领域的主导地位，刚毕业的人完全有可能希望继续使用 Chrome 操作系统。幸运的是，有许多优质的 Chromebook 设计精良，功能强大，足以使用多年。我们最喜欢的产品之一是 Acer 的 Chromebook Spin 714，该公司刚刚更新了英特尔的第 13 代酷睿处理器。它还有一个 14 英寸、1,920 x 1,200 的显示屏，比一般的 1080p 屏幕提供更多的垂直空间。添加一个坚固的键盘和触控板，您就拥有了一个不需要太多妥协的 Chromebook。我们还没有测试最新配置的电池寿命，但宏碁过去的 Chromebook 选项在该部门即使不是很出色，也很可靠。 </p><p><core-commerce id="2eb7148de89c41f3b00edc6b9efed1b2" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="614371ccb75241a1a0a96cb7ea196c47" data-type="product-list"></p><h2>平板电脑</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-04/1ba85f60-c7da-11ec-973a-f855b43834de" alt="三星的 Galaxy Tab S8，白色背景上的粉色和红色屏幕。" data-uuid="fb04b7de-e140-3a58-ae62-e41615ab9f91"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">三星</div></figure><p>在考虑平板电脑时，请抛开它们是否可以替代笔记本电脑的问题，并专注于它们最擅长的方面。它们可以是完成工作、将您的创造力与艺术和音乐制作应用程序结合起来或只是享受电影和游戏的绝佳选择。对于绝大多数人来说， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-ipads-how-to-pick-the-best-apple-tablet-for-you-150054066.html">Apple 的 iPad</a>是唯一值得考虑的平板电脑，即使他们不使用 Apple 产品也是如此。这要归功于久经考验的可靠硬件和庞大的软件库，其中包含数十万个针对 iPad 大屏幕优化的应用程序。</p><p>至于哪一款 iPad 最好， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS8yMDIyLUFwcGxlLWlQYWQtMTAtOS1pbmNoLVdpLUZpL2RwL0IwOVYzSE4xS0M_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8teTQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3OWYxOTlhLWM4MjEtNGZiMS05MzIxLTBmZTA4MGMyMGI0ZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWv3Zqku2hsRaq5B12k8palSNJS_-6osAkTp71nL_phj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2F2022-Apple-iPad-10-9-inch-Wi-Fi%2Fdp%2FB09V3HN1KC%3F">iPad Air</a>仍然是大多数人的正确选择——尤其是当你正在寻找一份好的毕业礼物时。虽然基本款 iPad 物超所值，但当你升级到 Air 时，你会得到很多。也许最重要的是，Air 拥有苹果的 M1 芯片，这是一款非常强大的平板电脑芯片，多​​年来一直在许多 Mac 中使用。这意味着 Air 速度极快，而且相当适合未来发展，尽管 Apple 的大部分硬件现在都在转向 M2。</p><p> iPad Air 的其他硬件的价格也令人印象深刻。它有一个 10.9 英寸的大屏幕，带有薄边框和抗反射涂层；显示器也直接层压在玻璃上，因此表面下方没有分散注意力的缝隙。 Air 包括 64GB 或 256GB 的存储空间、10 小时的电池续航时间、对第二代 Apple Pencil 和妙控键盘的支持以及改进的 12 兆像素前置摄像头。只需 599 美元，您就可以获得 iPad Pro 提供的几乎所有功能，而无需花费超过 800 美元。</p><p>但是，如果您正在购买 Android 顽固派， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvdGFibGV0cy9nYWxheHktdGFiLXM4L2J1eS8_IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3NzlmMTk5YS1jODIxLTRmYjEtOTMyMS0wZmUwODBjMjBiNGQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAARj_1U3PMfvkI6cH4-iAox9ONycCjH4smJvzN6hHKm0F&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftablets%2Fgalaxy-tab-s8%2Fbuy%2F%3F">三星的 Galaxy Tab S8</a>是一个不错的选择。 It features a high-resolution 11-inch screen with a 120Hz refresh rate, and has an S-Pen stylus included in the box. And while Android historically hasn&#39;t been the best option for large-screen devices, Samsung&#39;s Dex feature switches things up into a more desktop-like multi-window mode, which can be great for productivity. Samsung&#39;s built-in apps that take advantage of the S-Pen are solid as well. You might have a hard time finding apps that are designed for the Tab S8&#39;s larger screen, but if you&#39;re buying this for someone familiar with Android, they&#39;ll likely be aware of the trade-offs. </p><p><core-commerce id="ce5137881797492bbc08d88ecebaf9e5" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="dcb091c1667c4e0fa3596d2705c2a62a" data-type="product-list"></p><h2>智能手机</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-04/30d7f4e0-c7da-11ec-bfdb-fd8817a76151" alt="Six Google Pixel 6 Pro smartphones in various pastel colors on a gray table." data-uuid="259f1df1-de16-36e1-9802-1701c0cb0fe7"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>As useful as a laptop or tablet can be, chances are good that the most important computer people own is their smartphone. And if you know someone who is still rocking the same device they brought to campus with them four years ago, they&#39;ll definitely appreciate an upgrade. The good news is that it&#39;s pretty easy to pick out a phone that&#39;ll satisfy just about anyone, regardless of whether they prefer Android or iPhone.</p><p> This year, we&#39;re recommending the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0MTMwZTJmMC1hMTRmLTRjNWUtYmRhYi1jZDUyYWM3ZDhlNzkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXBwbGUuY29tL2lwaG9uZS0xNC1wcm8vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3NzlmMTk5YS1jODIxLTRmYjEtOTMyMS0wZmUwODBjMjBiNGQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAbtQbUklzOiNi1HfrNEMwUyocdrwgyj0HNb3h9KhsnxR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fiphone-14-pro%2F">iPhone 14 Pro</a> . The standard iPhone 14 is an excellent model, but the differences between the standard and Pro models are more pronounced this year than usual. The 14 Pro has an always-on display with a 120Hz refresh rate that can show you notifications and data from lock-screen widgets, and it also has a much better main camera than the iPhone 14. The Pro uses a 48-megapixel sensor, compared to the 12-megapixel one on the standard 14. Finally, the iPhone 14 Pro uses Apple&#39;s latest A16 Bionic processor, while the iPhone 14 is stuck with last year&#39;s A15. It&#39;s not a cheap phone at $999, but its extremely fast processor and Apple&#39;s track record of delivering software support for years means this investment should last a long time.</p><p> Samsung&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAX4Gs3buHSVG9rIp80RSlOSppaKzoPf3VUwvglOpgXZw&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Fsmartphones%2Fgalaxy-s23-ultra%2Fbuy%2Fgalaxy-s23-ultra-1tb-unlocked-sm-s918ulinxaa%2F">Galaxy S23 Ultra</a> is <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smartphones-140004900.html">our pick for Android users</a> . At $1,200, it&#39;s quite the pricey device, but it delivers everything you could ask for: a wonderful screen, improved cameras (including a wild 200-megapixel main sensor), excellent battery life and strong performance thanks to its Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 chip. Samsung worked with Qualcomm to create a custom version of that processor specifically for its Galaxy phones, and the end result is a phone that was up to 40 percent faster than its predecessor. Given how thoroughly Samsung dominates the Android space, this isn&#39;t a surprising recommendation, but it will make most Android fans happy.</p><p> If you want to save a little cash but still get a top-notch Android experience, <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtUHJvLVNtYXJ0cGhvbmUtVGVsZXBob3RvL2RwL0IwQkNRV1lSMlo_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8teTQtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3OWYxOTlhLWM4MjEtNGZiMS05MzIxLTBmZTA4MGMyMGI0ZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAActpz7tDLdIpOQ7KN8uo_UQwOTsIgoiH8Jh8uAKW8mPC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-Pro-Smartphone-Telephoto%2Fdp%2FB0BCQWYR2Z">Google&#39;s $899 Pixel 7 Pro</a> is definitely worth a look. It picks up where last year&#39;s Pixel 6 Pro left off, with the company&#39;s second-generation custom Tensor processor powering the whole affair. Performance and battery life remain excellent, although the smaller Pixel 7 gets slightly better battery life. The cameras are similar to those on the Pixel 6 Pro, which isn&#39;t a big problem, because Google consistently makes some of the best smartphone cameras out there. But the telephoto shooter got a big upgrade – it now offers 5x optical zoom. And the fact that this phone is built by Google means it&#39;ll get software updates before any other Android phone on the market.</p><p> Both of these phones are big (the Pixel 7 Pro&#39;s screen is 6.7 inches while the S23 Ultra has a 6.8-inch display), but the good news is that both Google and Samsung offer smaller-screened devices that keep most of the same features and specs as their larger siblings. You&#39;ll save some cash with a smaller device, too. </p><p><core-commerce id="262d0ac4d3f3496ebbf8f40892ba75c7" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="c9e80533594b43b48ff41adf27e72ac7" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="fb9ef14b6394489b8ce69822d1b2a4af" data-type="product-list"></p><h2>耳机</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/0cee3550-d205-11ec-bf1f-9b47cb9d42c7" style="" alt="WH-1000XM5 review" data-uuid="629db5d7-ec1e-3ad5-9043-3254d49d53d0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Almost anyone would benefit from a good pair of noise-canceling headphones, and once again Sony has made our <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-headphones-150030794.html">top pick</a> . <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAR_Pb8AP87g9WBL8URQWAwVLTees7Yr2Q6qukvQC37S5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-WH-1000XM5-Canceling-Headphones-Hands-Free%2Fdp%2FB09XS7JWHH">Sony&#39;s WH-1000XM5</a> , released about a year ago, is the best over-ear option on the market. At $400, they&#39;re more expensive than the XM4, but they offer a combination of incredible sound, a time-tested, refined design and excellent noise-canceling that is hard to beat. They also fit better and more comfortably than ever, and have 30 hours of battery life. The 1000XM5 looks better, sounds better and wears better than the previous model – it&#39;s hard to ask for much more.</p><p> This year, Sony has also made <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-earbuds-120058222.html">our favorite wireless earbuds</a> , the <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASE02RUr-gf9-RSzVmq-Ee0K3BNKRRcPsWfD_Zg2IUNR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-WF-1000XM4-Industry-Canceling-Headphones%2Fdp%2FB094C4VDJZ">WF-1000XM4</a> . As with its over-ear headphones, the $278 1000XM4 earbuds feature incredible sound quality, long battery life, excellent noise cancellation and a comfortable design. The battery life is particularly impressive – the earbuds can get about eight hours of playback with ANC active – that jumps up to 12 hours if you turn it off. Sony also included a host of smart software features like Speak-to-Chat automatic pausing, Adaptive Sound Control adjustments based on movement or location, 360 Reality Audio and a customizable EQ.</p><p> If you&#39;re buying earbuds for an Apple user, though, consider the second-generation <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAezHU8aid-suFqajn-21lZMlUjWzDdXLLVsJMVypn1zd&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApple-Generation-Cancelling-Transparency-Personalized%2Fdp%2FB0BDHWDR12%2F">AirPods Pro</a> . They don&#39;t quite beat Sony&#39;s WF-1000XM4 in sound quality or battery life, but there are a host of features that make them the best earbuds to use with an iPhone, iPad or Mac. The fast pairing tech Apple introduced with the first AirPods still makes it extremely easy to start using these earbuds, or to switch them seamlessly between different Apple devices. Both the case and buds are sweat and water resistant, making them a better option for workouts. These second-gen AirPods Pro also have big improvements in noise cancellation and sound quality, and the “transparency” mode that lets in outside sound lets you have a conversation or hear the world around you in a totally natural way. </p><p><core-commerce id="ab3c38616eed4b9e8c14b6c92eb9c3f1" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="f16ada4377cf43edbef717b59fd7f39f" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="51b2603bfc65485e84ec0d6a5d0a4541" data-type="product-list"></p><h2>监视器</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/44633e70-f02e-11ed-b95f-d5b827936068" style="" alt="LG 32UN650-W" data-uuid="35d54848-dc32-360a-a05e-7f29043a4f0a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> LG</div></figure><p> There are a dizzying number of monitors on the market, at basically any price point you can think of, which makes recommending a single monitor a very difficult task. Viewsonic currently makes one of our favorites, the <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZvK6Ezt-sZyrp_eHxglGa3LIttcFB2_Maxx6yIe6_ze&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FViewSonic-VP3268a-4K-Ergonomics-DisplayPort-Professional%2Fdp%2FB08TZVQBT5%2F">VP3268a-4K</a> . The 32-inch panel offers 4K resolution with excellent color accuracy (it&#39;s Pantone-validated and rated at Delta &lt;2 accuracy, for those who care about such things). Naturally, it has a host of connections including USB-C, HDMI and standard USB for hooking up peripherals. This model routinely sells for just under $800 on Amazon.</p><p> If you want a more affordable 32-inch option, consider the $430 <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAY7O-82RcaWU23X4AcnXQnfLjolelr9ZA9PjT72sFeBQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLG-32UN650-W-Compatibility-Borderless-Adjustable%2Fdp%2FB08FQ42MN1">LG 32UN650-W</a> . This was our favorite sub-$500 monitor, and it covers creative work, entertainment and gaming well. It supports AMD&#39;s Freesync technology, which helps eliminate screen tearing and stuttering in high-performance games. It also has a stand with tilt and height adjustments and built-in speakers, making it a pretty flexible option. </p><p><core-commerce id="ca62c987325f49dc82999ae368d207cc" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="e1d42b5fd8e34a8592400c311b96bf2b" data-type="product-list"></p><h2> Bags </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-04/042407c0-9c7c-11eb-b1e6-586f38c4db80" alt="A man in a blue suit holds a brown Waterfield Designs Executive Leather Messenger bag." data-uuid="9870fde9-7cce-375f-8b07-603013911625"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Waterfield</div></figure><p> As important as the right gear is, your grad also deserves something classy and stylish to carry all that stuff around. The <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.sfbags.com/collections/shoulder-messenger-bags/products/executive-leather-laptop-messenger">Executive Leather Messenger</a> from Waterfield Designs is an expensive choice, but it&#39;s worth the cost. Waterfield makes everything by hand in its San Francisco shop, and the materials it uses are top notch. I&#39;ve owned a lot of their products over the years, and I can safely say this bag will last a decade or more, and the leather will only look more attractive as time goes on.</p><p> On the inside are two padded slots, one for a tablet and one for a laptop. There are also two pockets, one zippered, as well as a pen slot and a metal key fob. Finally, there are two easily-accessible hand pockets under the flap, both with an extremely soft plush lining. The Executive Leather Messenger comes in three different leather colors and costs either $399 or $419, depending on which size you choose. It&#39;s an investment, for sure, but it will last a long time.</p><p> Waterfield&#39;s bags are typically quite pricey, but in the last year they released a new line of “essential” options that offer the company&#39;s excellent construction and smart features at a lower price point. The $179 <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.sfbags.com/products/essential-messenger-laptop-bag">Essential Messenger</a> is a lightweight option that does away with the leather and uses tough textiles instead. But its magnetic closures are fast and easy to undo, the strap is easily removable for wearing over whichever shoulder you choose, and it has foam inserts to help it keep its structure. There&#39;s a built-in sleeve for a laptop up to 14 inches, and I can confirm you can shove a surprising amount of gear in it considering its smaller size.</p><p> If you&#39;d prefer a non-leather choice, <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Peak Design;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=8747aed1-6586-46eb-856d-c95a5318901b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Peak+Design&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4NzQ3YWVkMS02NTg2LTQ2ZWItODU2ZC1jOTVhNTMxODkwMWIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGVha2Rlc2lnbi5jb20vY29sbGVjdGlvbnMvZXZlcnlkYXktYmFncy9wcm9kdWN0cy9ldmVyeWRheS1tZXNzZW5nZXI_dmFyaWFudD0yOTc0MTQzOTE4OTAzNiIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzc5ZjE5OWEtYzgyMS00ZmIxLTkzMjEtMGZlMDgwYzIwYjRkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAYHFH4Yc63Xxc6fygpfyl99f_y9255EChvTQJM7ioBV7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.peakdesign.com%2Fcollections%2Feveryday-bags%2Fproducts%2Feveryday-messenger%3Fvariant%3D29741439189036">Peak Design&#39;s Everyday Messenger</a> is a great and more affordable option. The $230 bag was originally designed for photographers, but (as the name implies) it works as a tough, well-designed option for whatever you need to carry. It has a dedicated 13-inch laptop sleeve and “stretchy” pockets that make it easier to keep track of smaller items. The bag also comes with a few flexible interior dividers so you can customize it in any way you want. The recently-released V2 update boasts 100 percent recycled outer fabric, a redesigned shoulder strap that should be less prone to slippage, a “MagLatch” magnetic buckle and a more efficient design that makes it 24 percent lighter than the original. </p><p><core-commerce id="fa75249f5de44ee4b825ea6690f35fce" data-type="product-list"></p><p><core-commerce id="d2d39fb1e1a14eed89a26b83df58a2e1" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-tech-upgrades-laptops-tablets-headphones-smartphones-monitors-bags-for-graduates-150049903.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-tech-upgrades-laptops-tablets-headphones-smartphones-monitors-bags-for-graduates-150049903.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 779f199a-c821-4fb1-9321-0fe080c20b4d</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 16 Jun 2023 14:45:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686926711</ingested><modified> 2023-06-16T14:45:20+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="1220" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/067842e0-f02e-11ed-9cfd-f792eb6a8106" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc